íŸ@f2724d867a68360a0d78e2c637f11317d3c2f97a6ef6ef5a6334020f47decf6e⁄!®Title: The last 2 weeks in Nushell #239
Path: Nushell
Content:
devyn made a LOT of improvements, mostly around plugins:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12236] introduced better generic errors for plugins (and perhaps scripts)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12204] allowed plugins to set environment variables in their caller's scope
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12244] refactored 
``PluginCustomValue::render_to_base_value_in``
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12234] merged stream_example into the example plugin and cleaned up names
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12218] added 
``Value::recurse_mut()``
 to save duplicated code in 
``PluginCustomValue``
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12213] supported custom values in plugin examples
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12185] made more robustness improvements to plugin persistence tests
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12177] disabled plugin GC tests on macOS
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12170] reorganized plugin API around commands
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12166] added environment engine calls for plugins
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12153] made the plugin persistence GC delay test more reliable
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12152] synced with the plugin garbage collector when setting config
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12144] fixed an unused IntoSpanned warning in nu_parser::parse_keywords when 'plugin' feature not enabled
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12182] fixed locking soundness in PersistentPlugin
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12122] improved the error message for a plugin version mismatch
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12088] supported all custom value operations on plugin custom values
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12064] kept plugins persistently running in the background
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12029] added support for engine calls from plugins
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12183] improved handling of EOF in MsgPack deserializer
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12266] miscellaneous documentation fixes
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12248] refactored PipelineDataHeader ‚áÑ PipelineData
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12237] fixed a broken build by replacing value_string() straggler
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12231] added support for 
``into string for custom values``
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12230] made custom value type handling more consistent
made EngineState clone cheaper with Arc on all heavy objects (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12229] 1
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12242] 2
)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12216] fixed zip signature to mention closure input type
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12120] changed the ignore command to use drain() instead of collecting a value
fdncred 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12258] bumped the rust-toolchain to 1.75.0
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12196] removed stdlib logging environment variables
.
JoaoFidalgo1403 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12251] fixed usage of the --tabs flag while converting to json
.
WindSoilder 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12241] removed the str escape-glob command
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12202] cleaned cp tests
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12201] removed test warnings
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12086] fixed ls with an empty string
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12056] made closure in 
``do``
 command support default parameters and type checking
.
sholderbach 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12240] refactored source cache into the 
``CachedFile``
 struct
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12198] updated contributor image generation with new upper bound
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12178] bumped 
``arboard``
 from 
``3.3.0``
 to 
``3.3.2``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12174] responded to nightly clippy
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12173] removed the rarely used std-lib issue template
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12172] minor refactored in 
``to html``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12171] refactored benches for more command benchmarks
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12165] included benchmarks in the CI clippy run
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12162] bumped 
``iana-time-zone``
 due to yanked locked version
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12158] removed outdated doccomment on 
``EngineState``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12151] disabled 
``fmt``
 feature of 
``polars(-core)``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12150] bumped 
``reedline``
 to dev (and 
``strum``
)
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12140] removed feat 
``extra``

and included it in default
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/11917] restructured 
``nu-protocol``
 into more meaningful units
.
YizhePKU 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12238] fixed a missing parse error when extra tokens were given to let bindings
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12235] fixed

inaccurate sleep duration
.
IanManske 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12228] used the rest argument in 
``export use``
 to match 
``use``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12227] fixed wrong stdout with 
``e>|``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12209] fixed 
``$in``
 value for 
``insert``
 closure
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12160] fixed ignored clippy lints
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12139] fixed clippy lints
, and

[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/11934] overhauled IO and redirection
.
sarubo 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12207] adjusted permissions using 
``umask``
 in 
``mkdir``
.
thomassimmer 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12197] fixed a histogram error message
.
zhiburt 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12184] used hex-dump for binary data in nu-explore
.
Tastaturtaste 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12179] used the system clipboard only for explicit copy/paste operations, addressing issue 11907
.
ysthakur 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12167] canonicalized each component of config files
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12136] canonicalized the config dir
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12134] updated tests Playground
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12118] used XDG_CONFIG_HOME before the default config directory
.
nils-degroot 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12149] improved the error message for 
``into sqlite``
 with empty records
.
kubouch 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12137] refactored nu-check
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/11441] continued to experiment with the debugger
.
hustcer 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12135] upgraded actions/checkout and softprops/action-gh-release
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12119] fixed Nu release packages

after upgrading to Nu v0.91
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12114] upgraded Nu to v0.91 for release and nightly workflow
.
rgwood 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12130] fixed up ctrl+C handling in 
``into_sqlite``
.
NowackiPatryk 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12128] fixed unexpected sqlite insert behavior (attempt 2)
.
wellweek 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12117] removed a repetitive word
.
FilipAndersson245 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12025] dived into extra benchmarks
.
dannou812 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/11948] fixed 
``to json -r``
 not removing whitespaces
.
rtpg 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/11654] allowed for stacks to have parents
.
lavafroth 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/11090] used environment variables to prevent the command_not_found from recursing
.
